## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="267ff-119">I telefoni sono lettere o simboli che descrivono i suoni di riconoscimento vocale.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="267ff-119">Phones are letters or symbols that describe the sounds of speech.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="267ff-120">Speech supporta tre alfabeti fonetici per specificare le pronunce personalizzate: il Universal Phone Set UPS (), il set di API riconoscimento vocale (SAPI) telefono e l'alfabeto fonetico internazionale (IPA).</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="267ff-120">System.Speech supports three phonetic alphabets for specifying custom pronunciations: the Universal Phone Set (UPS), the Speech API (SAPI) Phone set, and the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA).</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="267ff-121">I telefoni specificati nel <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Pronunciation%2A> deve corrispondere l'alfabeto fonetico specificato in <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsDocument.PhoneticAlphabet%2A>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="267ff-121">The phones specified in <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Pronunciation%2A> must match the phonetic alphabet specified in <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsDocument.PhoneticAlphabet%2A>.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="267ff-122">Visualizzare [dizionari e alfabeti fonetici](https://docs.microsoft.com/previous-versions/office/developer/speech-technologies/hh378335(v%3doffice.14)) per altre informazioni.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="267ff-122">See [Lexicons and Phonetic Alphabets](https://docs.microsoft.com/previous-versions/office/developer/speech-technologies/hh378335(v%3doffice.14)) for more information.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="267ff-123">I telefoni specificati nel <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Pronunciation%2A> indicare come il contenuto di <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Text%2A> dovrebbe risultare significativi per il riconoscimento ha esito positivo.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="267ff-123">The phones specified in <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Pronunciation%2A> indicate how the contents of <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Text%2A> should be pronounced for successful recognition.</span></span>  <span data-ttu-id="267ff-124">Il motore di riconoscimento vocale utilizza la pronuncia specificata nel <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Pronunciation%2A> in modo che corrisponda il riconoscimento vocale di input e restituisce la stringa contenuta dal <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Text%2A> nel risultato del riconoscimento.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="267ff-124">The speech recognition engine uses the pronunciation specified in <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Pronunciation%2A> to match speech input and returns the string contained by <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Text%2A> in the recognition result.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="267ff-125">Se i telefoni non sono delimitate da spazi o la stringa specificata contiene un numero di telefono non riconosciuto, il motore di riconoscimento non riconosce la pronuncia specificata come una pronuncia valida della parola contenuta <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Text%2A>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="267ff-125">If the phones are not space-delimited or the specified string contains an unrecognized phone, the recognition engine does not recognize the specified pronunciation as a valid pronunciation of the word contained by <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Text%2A>.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="267ff-126">Le pronunce specificate in <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Pronunciation%2A> hanno la precedenza sulle pronunce specificate in dizionari associate a una grammatica o a un motore di riconoscimento.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="267ff-126">Pronunciations specified in <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Pronunciation%2A> take precedence over pronunciations specified in lexicons associated with a grammar or a recognition engine.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="267ff-127">Inoltre, la pronuncia nel <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Pronunciation%2A> proprietà si applica solo a singola occorrenza della parola o frase contenuta <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Text%2A>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="267ff-127">Also, the pronunciation in the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Pronunciation%2A> property applies only to the single occurrence of the word or phrase contained by <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Text%2A>.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="267ff-128">Nell'esempio seguente la grammatica contiene parole gergo e ha anche una parola non comune: "whatchamacallit".</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="267ff-128">The grammar in the following example contains slang words and also has an uncommon word: "whatchamacallit".</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="267ff-129">Aggiunta di un pronuncia inline personalizzato, usando il <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Pronunciation%2A> proprietà del <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken> classe può migliorare l'accuratezza del riconoscimento per la parola "whatchamacallit" anche per quanto riguarda l'intera frase che lo contiene.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="267ff-129">Adding a custom, inline pronunciation using the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Pronunciation%2A> property of the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken> class can improve the accuracy of recognition for the word "whatchamacallit" as well as for the entire phrase that contains it.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="267ff-130">L'esempio Usa i telefoni dal Microsoft Universal Phone Set (UPS) per definire le pronunce personalizzate.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="267ff-130">The example uses phones from the Microsoft Universal Phone Set (UPS) to define the custom pronunciations.</span></span>  
  
```  
using System;  
using System.Speech.Recognition;  
using System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar;  
  
namespace SampleRecognition  
{  
  class Program  
  {  
    static void Main(string[] args)  
  
    // Initialize an instance of the in-process recognizer.  
    {  
      using (SpeechRecognitionEngine recognizer =  
         new SpeechRecognitionEngine(new System.Globalization.CultureInfo("en-US")))  
      {  
  
        // Build the SrgsOneOf objects with alternative choices for the slang phrase.  
        SrgsOneOf gimme = new SrgsOneOf(  
          new string[] { "give me", "gimme", "hand me", "ha'me" });  
        SrgsOneOf the = new SrgsOneOf(new string[] { "the", "duh" });  
  
        // Build the one-of element that contains the pronunciation.  
        SrgsItem thing = new SrgsItem("thingamajig");  
        SrgsItem whatcha = new SrgsItem();  
        SrgsToken callit = new SrgsToken("whatchamacallit");  
        callit.Pronunciation = "W AE T CH AE M AE K AA L IH T";  
        whatcha.Add(callit);  
        SrgsOneOf what = new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {thing, whatcha});  
  
        // Create the rule from the SrgsOneOf objects.  
        SrgsRule slangRule = new SrgsRule("slang", gimme, the, what);  
  
        // Build an SrgsDocument object from the rule and set the phonetic alphabet.  
        SrgsDocument tokenPron = new SrgsDocument(slangRule);  
        tokenPron.PhoneticAlphabet = SrgsPhoneticAlphabet.Ups;  
  
        // Create a Grammar object from the SrgsDocument and load it to the recognizer.  
        Grammar g_Slang = new Grammar(tokenPron);  
        g_Slang.Name = ("Slang Pronunciation");  
        recognizer.LoadGrammarAsync(g_Slang);  
  
        // Configure recognizer input.  
        recognizer.SetInputToDefaultAudioDevice();  
  
        // Attach a handler for the SpeechRecognized event.  
        recognizer.SpeechRecognized +=   
          new EventHandler<SpeechRecognizedEventArgs>(recognizer_SpeechRecognized);  
  
        // Start asynchronous recognition.  
        recognizer.RecognizeAsync();  
        Console.WriteLine("Starting asynchronous recognition...");  
  
        // Keep the console window open.  
        Console.ReadLine();  
      }  
    }  
  
    // Handle the SpeechRecognized event.  
    static void recognizer_SpeechRecognized(object sender, SpeechRecognizedEventArgs e)  
    {  
      Console.WriteLine("Recognized phrase: " + e.Result.Text);  
      Console.WriteLine("Confidence: " + e.Result.Confidence);  
      Console.WriteLine("  Word summary: ");  
      foreach (RecognizedWordUnit word in e.Result.Words)  
      {  
        Console.WriteLine(  
          "    Lexical form ({1})" +  
          " Pronunciation ({0})" +  
          " Confidence ({2})",  
          word.Pronunciation, word.LexicalForm, word.Confidence);  
      }  
    }  
  }  
}  
  
```
